SIMPLE: unmeaning
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unmeaning
<hw>Un*mean"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
no meaning or signification; <as>as, <ex>unmeaning</ex>
words</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not indicating intelligence or sense; senseless;
expressionless; <as>as, an <ex>unmeaning</ex> face</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There pride sits blazoned on the <qex>unmeaning</qex> brow.</q>
<rj><qau>Trumbull.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*mean"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*mean"ing*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unmeant</ent>⟦br⟧
